
    PHILA is on a mission to spread hope through song and prayer.Phila Madlingozi (29) has collaborated with DJ AJ on a single titled Bawo, which means God in Isixhosa.Phila is the son of Afro-soul musician Ringo Madlingozi and DJ AJ is the son of kwaito legend Arthur Mafokate.Phila said Bawo is a gospel-influenced house track taken from DJ AJ’s album, Legacy Volume 1.He said he and DJ AJ wanted to give people hope by praying for them.“This song will be a daily prayer. God will open your eyes, free you from your struggles and show you the way,” said Phila.He said the single, which is an affirmation of God’s power, will be enjoyed by anyone who needs to be comforted.“Those who love gospel music will sing and pray along and the house fans will dance to the beat.”Phila said he will be soon kick off a tour called Free Phila.“I will be performing all my unreleased songs, including the one inspired by the Fees Must Fall campaign.“It was produced by Buks of IV League fame and features rapper Solo.”Phila is known for playing the role of Sizwe on the Mzansi Magic drama series Isikizi.It was prophesied that Sizwe would marry his mum and kill his father, but the young king ran away because he did not want to fulfil the prophecies.Phila landed his first TV role in 2013 when he joined the SABC 1 drama series Intersexions.This is when people started to realise he was the son of Ringo Madlingozi.He said his role on the drama series opened doors for him. “After Intersexions, I played the role of Sthombe on Stepfather se Voet. One of the characters sleeps with his friend’s girlfriend, and the betrayed friend gets revenge by sleeping with his buddy’s mum.”Phila said although he and AJ are the sons of famous musicians, they are working hard to make names for themselves.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.ne